<section class="section" aria-labelledby="architecture-title">
  <header class="section-header">
    <h2 class="section-title" id="architecture-title">Architecture</h2>
  </header>
  
  <div class="grid-2">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Solved / Blank Pattern</h3>
      <p>Each day has two directories:</p>
      <pre><code>day-XX/
├── solved/     # Reference implementation
│   ├── main.cpp
│   ├── *.h
│   └── *.cpp
└── blank/      # Your attempt (write from memory)
    ├── main.cpp
    └── *.h / *.cpp (as needed)</code></pre>
      <p>Workflow: Study <code>solved/</code> → Close it → Implement in <code>blank/</code> → Diff → Annotate gaps.</p>
    </article>
    
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Retrieval Testing Loop</h3>
      <div class="architecture-diagram">Study solved/ (15–30 min)
    │
    ▼
Close all references
    │
    ▼
Write blank/ from memory
    │
    ▼
Diff: solved/ vs blank/
    │
    ├─► Missing?  → Annotate: "forgot bounds check"
    ├─► Wrong?    → Annotate: "off-by-one in loop"
    ├─► Better?   → Annotate: "used algorithm, cleaner"
    └─► Style?    → Annotate: "naming inconsistent"
    │
    ▼
Commit both + annotations
    │
    ▼
Next day</div>
    </article>
  </div>
  
  <article class="card" style="margin-top: var(--space-5);">
    <h3>Why This Works</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Active recall</strong> > passive re-reading. The struggle to reconstruct strengthens memory traces.</li>
      <li><strong>Immediate feedback</strong> from the diff — no waiting for a grader.</li>
      <li><strong>Metacognition</strong> — annotation forces you to name the gap: "I forgot to validate input" vs "I didn't know."</li>
      <li><strong>Artifact trail</strong> — the commit log shows progression, not just final state. Retry commits are visible.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</section>